The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Business Briefs
                                                                                                               Business Briefs
                              
	 New Delhi, June 15: Oil companies today hiked jet fuel prices 12 per cent, an increase which may lead to a rise in fares. Prices in Calcutta will rise to Rs 44,289 per kilolitre from Rs 40,230.05 per kl, while in Chennai it has been raised to Rs 40,024 per kl from Rs 35,821.34 per kl. In Mumbai, it will go up from Rs 33,260.8 per kl to Rs 37,367 per kl.                            
	 New Delhi, June 15: The government today said that a company suffering from losses for three consecutive years and with a negative net worth might be delisted from the stock exchanges. This leads to an amendment of the Securities Contracts Regulation Act, providing an operational framework for voluntary or compulsory delisting of companies.                            
	 Hyderabad, June 15: Dr Reddys Laboratories today announced a strategic partnership with GlaxoSmithKline. The multinational branded drug maker will sell the domestic generic firms products in Africa, West Asia, Latin America and Asia Pacific markets, excluding India.                            
	 Calcutta, June 15: Swiss ambassador Philippe Welti today met chief minister Buddhadeb Bhattacharjee to discuss possible business opportunities for Swiss companies in the city.                            
	 New Delhi, June 15: TVS Motors today launched the Apache RTR bike having a 180cc engine and priced at Rs 63,990 (ex-showroom, Delhi).                                                                                                                           
